### What To Customize For Fractal Branding

|File                   |What To Change                                           |
|-----------------------|---------------------------------------------------------|
|`index.html`           |Title, meta description, welcome message text            |
|`css/style.css`        |Background color, font, overall aesthetic                |
|`css/bar.css`          |Search bar appearance, placeholder text                  |
|`css/welcome.css`      |Landing message (“Wikipedia Map” → “Fractal”)            |
|`js/wikipedia_parse.js`|Replace entirely with `fractal_api.js`                   |
|`js/help.js`           |Update tutorial text to describe Fractal, not Wikipedia  |
|`js/main_functions.js` |Node colors — map domain colors to Fractal’s color scheme|

**Node color logic** lives in `main_functions.js`. Currently colors nodes by distance from center. For Fractal you’ll want to color by:

- Domain nodes → their assigned color (blue, green, etc.)
- Emergent/grey node → grey
- Tension edges → styled differently than regular connections

-----

### What To Keep Exactly As-Is

- All of `vis.js` graph rendering
- `bindings.js` — click/keypress handling works perfectly
- `network_serialize.js` — share-by-URL feature is a great free feature to keep
- `commafield.js` — multi-topic input is useful for Fractal too
- `modals.js` and `progress.js` — loading states and modals are needed

