## Brutalist Search Input — Final Version (from Uiverse.io by 0xnihilism — customized for Fractal)

Replaces the current commafield search bar. Type and hit Enter to create a brutalist blue tag. Hover a tag to reveal the ✕ delete button. Backspace on empty input deletes the last tag. Border pulses between Fractal blue and purple on focus.

### Behavior

- Type anything → hit **Enter** → creates a blue brutalist square tag
- **Hover** a tag → ✕ appears → **click** to delete it
- **Backspace** on empty input → deletes last tag
- Border pulses `#4A90D9` ↔ `#7B6CF6` while focused
- No label — clean and minimal

### Implementation Notes

- Replace the `.commafield` div and `commafield.js` entirely with this
- The `#field` div acts as the container, `#typing` is the real input
- Tags are created dynamically via JS — no library needed
- When user clicks Map, collect all `.search-tag span:first-child` text values as the query array
- Width should be `100%` inside `#formbox`

### Collect tags for Map button

```javascript
function getSearchTags() {
  const tags = document.querySelectorAll('.search-tag span:first-child');
  return Array.from(tags).map(t => t.textContent.trim());
}
// Returns array like ["why do empires fall", "democracy"]
```

### Full Code

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<style>
  .brutalist-container {
    position: relative;
    width: 100%;
    font-family: monospace;
  }

  .brutalist-field {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 6px;
    width: 100%;
    padding: 12px 16px;
    font-size: 16px;
    font-weight: bold;
    color: #ffffff;
    background-color: #0f0f1a;
    border: 4px solid #4A90D9;
    outline: none;
    transition: all 0.3s cubic-bezier(0.25, 0.8, 0.25, 1);
    box-shadow: 5px 5px 0 #000, 10px 10px 0 #4A90D9;
    min-height: 52px;
    cursor: text;
    box-sizing: border-box;
  }

  .brutalist-field:focus-within {
    animation: focus-pulse 4s cubic-bezier(0.25, 0.8, 0.25, 1) infinite;
  }

  .search-tag {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 6px;
    background-color: #4A90D9;
    color: #ffffff;
    font-family: monospace;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 0.82em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    padding: 4px 10px;
    border: 2px solid #000000;
    border-radius: 0;
    box-shadow: 3px 3px 0 #000000;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: all 0.15s ease;
    white-space: nowrap;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .search-tag:hover {
    background-color: #7B6CF6;
    translate: 1px 1px;
    box-shadow: 2px 2px 0 #000000;
  }

  .search-tag .delete-x {
    font-size: 0.9em;
    opacity: 0;
    max-width: 0;
    overflow: hidden;
    transition: max-width 0.2s ease, opacity 0.2s ease;
  }

  .search-tag:hover .delete-x {
    opacity: 1;
    max-width: 20px;
    padding-left: 2px;
  }

  .brutalist-typing {
    flex: 1;
    min-width: 80px;
    background: transparent;
    border: none;
    outline: none;
    color: #ffffff;
    font-family: monospace;
    font-size: 16px;
    font-weight: bold;
    caret-color: #4A90D9;
    padding: 2px 0;
  }

  .brutalist-typing::placeholder { color: #444466; }
  .brutalist-typing:focus::placeholder { color: transparent; }

  @keyframes focus-pulse {
    0%, 100% { border-color: #4A90D9; box-shadow: 5px 5px 0 #000, 10px 10px 0 #4A90D9; }
    50%       { border-color: #7B6CF6; box-shadow: 5px 5px 0 #000, 10px 10px 0 #7B6CF6; }
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="brutalist-container">
    <div class="brutalist-field" id="field" onclick="document.getElementById('typing').focus()">
      <input class="brutalist-typing" id="typing" type="text" placeholder="Ask Fractal anything..." />
    </div>
  </div>

  <script>
    const input = document.getElementById('typing');
    const field = document.getElementById('field');

    input.addEventListener('keydown', function(e) {
      if (e.key === 'Enter' && this.value.trim() !== '') {
        e.preventDefault();
        createTag(this.value.trim());
        this.value = '';
      }
      if (e.key === 'Backspace' && this.value === '') {
        const tags = field.querySelectorAll('.search-tag');
        if (tags.length > 0) tags[tags.length - 1].remove();
      }
    });

    function createTag(text) {
      const tag = document.createElement('div');
      tag.className = 'search-tag';
      tag.innerHTML = '<span>' + text + '</span><span class="delete-x">✕</span>';
      tag.addEventListener('click', function() { this.remove(); input.focus(); });
      field.insertBefore(tag, input);
    }

    function getSearchTags() {
      const tags = document.querySelectorAll('.search-tag span:first-child');
      return Array.from(tags).map(t => t.textContent.trim());
    }
  </script>
</body>
</html>
```

