## Edge Relationship Card — Draggable with Tether (Final Version)

Appears when a user clicks the line connecting two nodes. Shows the relationship between them with a dashed tether line connecting the card back to the midpoint of the node-to-node edge. Fully draggable.

### Behavior

- Card floats and can be dragged anywhere on screen
- Dashed animated tether connects card center to midpoint of the node edge
- Small dot marks the midpoint on the node edge
- “More Details” dropdown reveals reasons + “if this link broke” section
- “Explore Both” spawns two separate draggable node cards (blue + purple)
- Close button is brutalist dark with red hover

### Relationship Badge Types

- `drives` — blue `#4A90D9`
- `tension` — red `#E05C5C`
- `supports` — green `#50C878`
- `constrains` — amber `#ffaa00`

### Implementation Notes

- On vis.js edge click, get `edge.from` and `edge.to` node names and the relationship label
- Position card near the midpoint of the edge
- Tether midpoint = `(nodeA.x + nodeB.x) / 2, (nodeA.y + nodeB.y) / 2`
- Update tether on every drag move event
- “Explore Both” opens two node cards with the existing `.node-card` component

